\section{Food and agriculture}
\label{sec:personal_action_food_ag}
%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%

Chapter~\ref{chap:food_and_agriculture} shows that the animal-based portions of the
agriculture system are less efficient than the overall system.
So eating fewer animal-products and more plant-based products provides
improved agriculture system efficiency and a net sustainability benefit.
I.e., eating closer to the bottom of the food chain brings sustainability benefits.
In short, more people should eat less meat, and
more people should be vegetarians.

Resources to help with a personal transition to eating less meat include
vegetarian cookbooks such as \emph{The Simply Vegetarian Cookbook}~\cite{Pridmore:2018ts},
**** more here ****,
and philosophical treatments of the matter such as \emph{Philosophy Comes to Dinner}~\cite{Chignell:2016vj}.


